	(text_box "The ROLE signal is used determine if a board is a primary or secondary system via hardware. It is pulled down to GND by default which indicates the board is a \"primary\" board. Once a bridge is formed between two boards, a loop is closed for the secondary board through the primary board which then pulls the ROLE line high.\n\nThis ROLE is used primarily to disable the secondary microcontroller so it doesn't interfere with normal operation as well as assign the secondary system's power monitor a different I^{2}C address. The RPi can read ROLE to determine state as well."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 12.7 55.88 0)
		(size 50.8 46.8855)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "67cff582-b524-4f56-a77b-1ae9107414b4")
	)
